<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>DT/DTA-466 Diesel Engine Service (1990) - ROCKER ARM ASSEMBLY, CAMSHAFT, TAPPETS AND PUSH RODS - CAMSHAFT,
        TAPPETS &#38; PUSH RODS - REMOVAL
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="6">
        <title>REMOVAL</title>
        <para>Refer to the appropriate manual section for removal procedures and remove the following:</para>
        <randlist type="bullet">
            <item>
                <para>Crossover pipe</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Fuel injection lines (high pressure)</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Fuel leak-off lines (low pressure)</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Fuel injection nozzles</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Aneroid tube</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Intake manifold</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Turbocharger</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Thermostat housing and thermostat</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Valve cover</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Rocker arm assembly</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Push rods</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Cylinder head</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Injection pump</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Vibration damper and pulley</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Oil pump</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Water pump pulley</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Water pump</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Oil pan and pick-up tube</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Engine front cover</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Crankcase breather tube</para>
            </item>
        </randlist>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove valve tappets or roller tappets and roller tappet guides from their bores. Refer to
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef4150517">5.17</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                .
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Mark the tappets as to location in the engine block, so they can be returned to their original
                        position.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Rotate the engine until the timing marks on the camshaft gear, crankshaft gear and idler
                gear are aligned as shown in
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef4150518">5.18</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                .
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Prior to camshaft removal, mount a magnetic base dial indicator on the front of the engine
                and check camshaft gear backlash (
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef4150519">5.19</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                ). If backlash exceeds specified limits (see
                <hotlnk document="e415_HL4150501.xml" xrefid="hl4150501">"SPECIFICATIONS"</hotlnk>), replace the
                camshaft gear.
            </para>
            <figure id="ef4150517" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="cg11889" filename="../figcg1/cg11889.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 5.17 Roller Tappet and Roller Tappet Guide Removal.</caption>
            </figure>
            <figure id="ef4150518" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="cg12080" filename="../figcg1/cg12080.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 5.18 Align Gear Train Timing Marks (Early Style Front Plate Shown).</caption>
            </figure>
            <figure id="ef4150519" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="cg12081" filename="../figcg1/cg12081.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 5.19 Measure Camshaft Gear Backlash.</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Check the camshaft gear backlash as follows:</para>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Position the dial indicator tip @ a gear tooth end remove lash.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">"Zero" the dial indicator.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Hold the idler gear steady and move the camshaft gear by hand. Read the indicator and
                    record the backlash.
                </para>
            </step2>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Reposition the dial indicator and check camshaft end play (
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef4150520">5.20</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                ) as follows:
            </para>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Position the dial indicator tip on the camshaft hub.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Push the camshaft toward the rear of the engine.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">"Zero" the dial indicator.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Place a small pry bar between the camshaft gear and the front plate. Push the gear out
                    and read the end play on the dial indicator.
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Compare the dial indicator reading with the specifications.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Remove the dial indicator. If end play exceeds specified limits (see
                    <hotlnk document="e415_HL4150501.xml" xrefid="hl4150501">"SPECIFICATIONS"</hotlnk>), replace the
                    camshaft thrust plate.
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>Turn the engine stand so the front of the engine is facing up (engine in vertical
                            position). This position allows for easy removal of the camshaft assembly.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step2>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Rotate the camshaft gear so the access holes in the gear align with the thrust plate
                retaining bolts.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the two thrust plate bolts and washers. Refer to
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef4150521">5.21</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                .
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the camshaft from the crankcase by lifting the assembly straight up. Refer to
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef4150522">5.22</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                .
                <emph type="bold"></emph>
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>This method reduces the risk damaging the camshaft journals and/or bushings.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <figure id="ef4150520" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="cg12082" filename="../figcg1/cg12082.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 5.20 Check Camshaft End Play.</caption>
            </figure>
            <figure id="ef4150521" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="cg12083" filename="../figcg1/cg12083.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 5.21 Remove Thrust Plate Bolts.</caption>
            </figure>
            <figure id="ef4150522" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="cg12084" filename="../figcg1/cg12084.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 5.22 Remove Camshaft.</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
